deck: The Armor Tony created after Bleeding Edge was removed from his system. It was made to function as modular armor.
description:
Origin

Stark decided to create new types of tech so he invented new Iron-man Amor in Black and Gold colors which is powered by large number of Repulsor Tech cores. One unique thing about this armor is that the color of Repulsor Tech Cores and Repulsor Rays is red instead of yellow or blue.

Abilities

It can be stored in a briefcase in the form of liquid metal and change it's shape in form of Armor around Stark almost instantly while being activated. The armor can be overridden in order to respond to whoever it is needed through the use of special code "Hdgk(X)=H2k(X,Q)∩Hk,k(X)".

When Stark joined Guardians of the Galaxy, he used the tech given to him by Rocket Raccoon to allow him to remotely control the armor on Earth when his help is extremly needed while being several light years away with Guardians of the Galaxy.

While the armor still contains usually abilities as other armors like repulsors, Uni-Beam (stronger than ever with this armor), electricity discharge, yet busters to allow flight as well as superhuman levels of strength, speed and durability, amor's primary function is the ability to attach and de-attach different kind of modules and equipment from different purposes depending on the situation which allows Stark to use different types of technology without the need of creating special armors for different task at hand. To access of modular ability and to adapt the armor to different types of technology the suit needs the aid of Stark's newest A.I. called H.E.L.E.N.

Modules Used by this armor

  • Explosive launcher.
  • Hacking device.
  • Back thrust gear.
  • Mini Gun powered by repulsor tech.
  • Misssiles fired from wrists.
  • EMP defence.
  • Sonic Distruptor.
  • Taser laster gun.

Merchandise

  • Hasbro released an Iron-man figure in this armor as part of Avengers: Age of Ultron Movie Hulkbuster "Build-A-Figure" wave for Marvel Legends line.

deck: Synth-Kinetic Interfacing Nano-Fluid (S.K.I.N.) is a material created by Tony Stark and used to coat the Iron Man Armor until it was compromised by Ultron.
description: Synth-Kinetic Interfacing Nano-Fluid (S.K.I.N.) was created by Tony Stark when he began working at Askew & Stark. It was created to be the cutting edge in polymer-based nano-tech smart allow design. The substance was capable of expanding from a small cap-like delivery system to cover any material thus imparting its strengths to the coated object. As such, it allowed such objects to maintain their inherent aesthetic and interior physical properties but with the added capabilities provided by S.K.I.N. The material was noted for being almost as strong as Adamantium yet supple at the same time. Tony Stark made use of an Iron Man Armor coated with S.K.I.N. for a time until Ultron co-opted the substance for his own use. The Mechanical villain attempted to use it as a weapon of mass destruction on Earth and after his defeat Stark abandoned the use of S.K.I.N. technology.
name: S.K.I.N.

description:
As the name implies, the Hulkbuster was a specific variant of the Iron Man Armor designed to combat the Hulk.

In Other Media

Television

The Incredible Hulk: The Animated Series

The Hulkbuster armor appears in the Incredible Hulk: The Animated Series episode "Helping Hand, Iron Fist".

Iron Man: Armored Adventures

The Hulkbuster suit appears in the Iron Man: Armored Adventures episode "Uncontrollable", where Tony builds it to contend with the rampaging Hulk. The suit is even larger and more fortified than the War Machine armor.

The Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes

The Hulkbuster armor appears several times in The Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes, starting in the episode "Everything is Wonderful", where Tony uses it to battle Wonder Man. A more advanced model reappears in the two-part episode "The Ultron Imperative", where it is shown as one of the models hijacked by Ultron before being obliterated by Thor. A rebuilt model is shown in the second season episode "The Deadliest Man Alive", where Tony is forced to use it to battle the out of control Hulk.

Film

Iron Man & Hulk: Heroes United

The Hulkbuster armor appears in the animated film Iron Man & Hulk: Heroes United, where it is controlled by Zzzax and used to battle the Hulk and Iron Man.

Iron Man 3

A suit of armor similar to the Hulkbuster appears in Iron Man 3. Dubbed the Igor, it is one of the new suits Tony builds as part of his Iron Legion. It is used during the final battle against Aldrich Killian and his Extremis soldiers, and is presumably destroyed when Tony activates the self-destruct sequence he installed in the Iron Legion.

Avengers: Age of Ultron

The Hulkbuster armor appears in Avengers: Age of Ultron, where it is referred to as "Veronica," in reference to the Archie Comics character. It is used by Tony to subdue the Hulk after Bruce Banner is driven mad by Scarlet Witch's powers.

Video Games

The Incredible Hulk

The Hulkbuster armor appears in the video game adaptation of The Incredible Hulk, though it is not present in the film itself. The suit is essentially a palette swap of the Hulk himself, and possesses similar abilities and attributes.

Iron Man 2

The Hulkbuster armor is a playable suit in the video game adaptation of Iron Man 2, though it does not actually appear in the movie.

Lego Marvel Super Heroes

The Hulkbuster armor appears in Lego Marvel Super Heroes.

Disney Infinity 3.0

The Hulkbuster is playable in Disney Infinity 3.0 as part of the "Marvel Battlegrounds" expansion.

Merchandise

Toys

  • A Hulkbuster figure was released for Toy Biz's line for the original Iron Man animated series.
  • Hasbro released various Hulkbuster figures to promote Age of Ultron. One was the subject of a "Build-a-Figure" wave for the Marvel Legends line, which could be assembled after purchasing the seven figures in the line (Marvel NOW! Iron Man, Doctor Strange, Vision, Blizzard, Valkyrie, Thundra and War Machine), each of which came with a piece of the Hulkbuster.
  • Hot Toys released a large, ultra-detailed Hulkbuster figure based off its appearance in Age of Ultron.
  • Lego released a Hulkbuster kit for the company's line of Age of Ultron products.

Statues

  • Bowen Designs released a Hulkbuster statue depicting the armor's classic comic appearance.
  • Kotobukiya released a Hulkbuster statue as part of the company's ARTFX line.

description:
Overview

Sage wears a pair of custom-built cyber shades that function as a wireless broadband computer network among like models. The shades provide an audio/video feed via an in-built computer system outfitted with miniaturized conventional microphones and cameras, and can also project a three-dimensional image into the visual field of the wearer that can be expanded to allow others to see with whom the wearer is communicating or information they are reviewing.

The shades provide input by means of a virtual reality iconographic keyboard, and have an alternate visual input system for when a user’s hands are otherwise occupied. The shades can be interfaced with any external data network whether terrestrial or alien in origin. The shades also possess various sensors for detecting telepathic resonance patterns, tracking energy trails, and analyzing electronic circuitry, among others.

deck: Brzk or Berserk is a drug developed on Apokolips by DeSaad that is composed of quasi-sentient organic nanites that transform their user into a berserker warrior and/or living bomb.
description: Brzk is a new super drug invented by the torture specialist of the Darkseid's Elite, Desaad of Apokolips. The drug is, in actuality, a cluster of microscopic quasi-sentient organic nanotechnology. All of which have a base menial consciousness of their own and are highly influential as they are also quite open to mental suggestion, once bonded to an individuals system they begin altering their very biological structure producing a very dangerous berserker warrior of enhanced strength and toughness. The Drugs effects are dual phased in process the first phase transforms in-takers into savage feral supersoldier's, second phase causes their bodily chemistry to mesh and react dangerously with the Berserk in their system causing them to spontaneously combust exploding with devastating force. Enough to level a small apartment complex with just three Berserk users.
name: Brzk

deck: Armstrong's satchel is bottomless and contains many items he gathered in his life.
description:
During the event called Unity, Armstrong lost the satchel in a pile of pterodactyl dung. When he and Archer were transported back to Los Angeles at the end of Unity, the satchel reappeared there also. However, it was unnoticed by The Sect, who had captured Archer and Armstrong upon their arrival in LA. A young street kid named Daryll picked it up and leered inside it, giving him the power of persuasion. Bragging about it to his friend Kevin Hudson, Kevin snatched the satchel and used it for his own selfish purposes. After several days, Kevin encountered a severely burned Mahmud, all wrapped up, resembling a mummy. Mahmud was insensitive to Kevin's powers and took the satchel from him.

Contents

According to Armstrong, the satchel contains the Eye of the Sphinx and the trinkets of the gods, the Holy Grail and universes within universes, the very secrets of life itself.

What has been seen pulled out of it:

  • The Eye of the Medusa, which turns people into stone if they look into the eye
  • The Wand of Circe, which will turn people into pigs when the enchantment is said
  • A gold goblet
  • An electrical gun made by the Nicola Tesla Company
  • The Book of Geomancers

deck:
A Sacred Gear bestowed upon Issei and activated when he is resurrected as a devil.

It posses the power to double the wielder's overall power every 10 seconds.
description:
The Boosted Gear is a Sacred Gear wielded by Hyudou Issei and listed as one of the 13 Longinus. It contains the spirit of Ddraig, the Red Dragon Emperor.

The Boosted Gear has 3 known gauntlet forms (plus an extra hybrid form), each with its unique abilities. Boosted Gear's Balance Breaker "Scale Male" covers the user's entire body.

Gauntlet Form

Twice Critical

- The Boosted Gear's first from, it doubles the wielder's power.

Boosted Gear

- Same as Twice Critical but now it doubles the user's power every 10 seconds.

Boosted Gear "Gift"

- It retains the ability of its previous forms, but now, the power accumulated can be transferred to an ally.

Dividing Gear

- Attains when Issei placed one of Albion's Jewel in his Boosted Gear attaining the power of Divine Dividing.

Balance Breaker (Scale Mail) Form

Attained by sacrificing Issei's left hand to Ddraig
name: Boosted Gear

Origin

Fearing he might learn compassion and nobility from the omniscience offered from the eyes, Mephisto opted to dull their effect by instead giving them to an unsuspecting fool, such as Nighthawk; who was tricked to believing the eyes would enable him to see crimes before they were committed and prevent them.

Creation

The Eyes of Mephisto were created by Jim Krueger and Richard Case and first appeared in Nighthawk #1.
